messages.content:
Griff Green🌱, [20.04.21 16:50]
We aren't asking TE's to come do work... we are asking them to make an impact investment 

If they are busy, then thats all they need to do, and they are advancing token engineering by just hodling.

Griff Green🌱, [20.04.21 16:55]
If they want to put in 1 hour a month towards advancing token engineering they can vote

But voting here is not like the normal yes no voting you thing of, its conviction voting which will be more like how people donate with gitcoin... 

but instead of donating its voting (no loss to you, just using your governance rights you get as a token holder) 

and instead of it being about all things web3 like on gitcoin its focused on Token Engineering public goods

And if you and the rest of the community do a good job and make more people want to be part of this movement, then you will also make money while advancing token engineering.

Griff Green🌱, [20.04.21 17:28]
And if you want to take it the next level... you can actively participate... 

This org is likely to become the Schelling point for the TE Community. 

Let's say you want the superfluid cadCAD models to get infront of the eyes of the TE Community and to be the standard design template that all TE's use for streaming money.... 

Well you make a proposal requesting $1000 to clean up, document, generalize, and open source the models....

Not because you need the money... but because you want to to get the TEC stamp of support and awareness.
